records.addlTxt: signed, Order for Inpatient Competency Examination

Defendant Drucilla Rose Jackson not in court, in custody.  Attorney Corey R. Flynn in court for Drucilla Rose Jackson.  Prosecuting attorney Foley J. Van Lieshout Ms. in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy court clerk cmt. 
Deputy Court Clerk: cmt
Case in court for return on doctors report. Parties do not contest the report.The Court found that an inpatient examination is necessary and committed the defendant to one of the two state mental health institutes 
for a competency examination and report pursuant to Sec. 971.14(2)(3) of Wisconsin Statutes. Case adjourned for return on doctors report, Branch 15.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for November 15, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

Defendant Drucilla Rose Jackson not in court, in custody.  Attorney Corey R. Flynn in court for Drucilla Rose Jackson.  Prosecuting attorney Navjot Singh Hira in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy court clerk cmt. 
Statements by defense counsel that defendant has pending case 21CM2013 scheduled for return on doctor report in Branch 17 and wishes to raise competency on this case and use that report. State has no objection to Court using the doctor report for pending case. Court grants and orders case adjourned for return on doctor report, 10-21-2022 at 1:30 pm, Branch 15.

Defendant Drucilla Rose Jackson not in court, in custody.  Attorney Corey R. Flynn appeared by video for Drucilla Rose Jackson.  Prosecuting attorney Arthur Kenneth Thexton in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
CASE HEARD OFF THE RECORD DUE TO COURT REPORTER AVAILABILITY.
Case in court for status conference. Court waived defendant's appearance.
Attorney Flynn informed the Court that competency was raised in matter 21CM2013 which is assigned to Branch 17.
Due to court reporter availability, Court orders a status conference scheduled in person to allow attorney Flynn to raise competency on the record.
Court ordered case adjourned for status conference in Branch 15.
Status conference scheduled for October 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for October 21, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Drucilla Rose Jackson not in court, in custody.  Prosecuting attorney Navjot Singh Hira in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy court clerk cmt.
Off the record. Defendant appearance waived. Case scheduled for pretrial conference. SPD has not yet appointed counsel. Case adjourned for status of counsel by Zoom, Branch 15.
Status conference scheduled for October 11, 2022 at 10:30 am.

Court ordered no contact with AJ.
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5. Court advised Defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Drucilla Rose Jackson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Colleen A Taylor appeared by video for Drucilla Rose Jackson.  Attorney Michael J. Odden appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Case retabbed due to nature of the case. Defendant is advised this case is reassigned to Judge J.D. Watts, Branch 15.   Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned to Branch 15 for pretrial conference.
